506
00:25:06.125 --> 00:25:08.083
don't go up the stairs. ever.

507
00:25:09.083 --> 00:25:10.309
Who'd be stupid enough to do that?

508
00:25:10.333 --> 00:25:11.333
No one!

509
00:25:36.417 --> 00:25:37.958
Vanessa Friedman in <i>The Times</i>

510
00:25:38.042 --> 00:25:41.333
says that Andy's story
is a "bracing mea culpa."

511
00:25:41.417 --> 00:25:44.333
Yeah. but did anyone
besides culture writers

512
00:25:44.417 --> 00:25:46.000
actually click on the story?

513
00:25:46.083 --> 00:25:49.833
Not really. but optics-wise.
saved our bacon. right?

514
00:25:49.917 --> 00:25:51.417
We'll see. Jury's still out.

515
00:26:01.458 --> 00:26:02.833
- Good morning.
- Hi.

516
00:26:08.667 --> 00:26:09.708
Nigel in?

517
00:26:10.208 --> 00:26:12.208
No. Nigel's not in.

518
00:26:18.375 --> 00:26:19.415
- I read your piece.
- Hmm?

519
00:26:19.458 --> 00:26:20.809
I read your piece. It was really good.

520
00:26:20.833 --> 00:26:22.500
Oh. thank you.

521
00:26:23.500 --> 00:26:25.625
Oh. See. that was a cool profile.

522
00:26:25.708 --> 00:26:27.833
{\an8}Oh. yeah. The Barnes piece.

523
00:26:27.917 --> 00:26:30.583
Obviously. it was from before their split.

524
00:26:30.667 --> 00:26:31.583
Yeah.

525
00:26:31.667 --> 00:26:33.417
- I love Sasha Barnes.
- I know.

526
00:26:33.500 --> 00:26:34.809
I've tried to get
an interview with her.

527
00:26:34.833 --> 00:26:36.792
like. a million times
but I've always struck out.

528
00:26:36.875 --> 00:26:38.875
- Oh. you're not the only one.
- Really?

529
00:26:38.958 --> 00:26:40.125
Miranda would kill.

530
00:26:40.208 --> 00:26:43.250
Now that their divorce has made Sasha
one of the richest women in the world.

531
00:26:43.333 --> 00:26:44.833
Interesting.

532
00:26:44.917 --> 00:26:47.583
I feel like I could write a book about
just his before and after.

533
00:26:47.667 --> 00:26:48.667
You know what I mean?

534
00:26:48.750 --> 00:26:50.518
The original Benji Barnes was.
like. that slope-shouldered

535
00:26:50.542 --> 00:26:53.792
nerd who's like. never seen
the inside of a weight room.

536
00:26:53.875 --> 00:26:55.643
Lately... There was a picture
of him the other day.

537
00:26:55.667 --> 00:27:00.042
A few steroids. a smidge
of Sculptra. some Ozempic

538
00:27:00.125 --> 00:27:01.583
- and voilà.
- He's a modern miracle.

539
00:27:01.667 --> 00:27:02.958
It's a modern miracle.

540
00:27:03.042 --> 00:27:04.250
Gotta love a glow up.

541
00:27:04.333 --> 00:27:05.333
It's compelling.

542
00:27:06.500 --> 00:27:08.917
Okay. well... Ooh. Hi.

543
00:27:15.500 --> 00:27:18.250
We took some vintage Muglers
and Westwoods.

544
00:27:18.333 --> 00:27:21.042
and we shot them downtown
in the Washington Mews.

545
00:27:21.125 --> 00:27:22.208
And you were there

546
00:27:22.958 --> 00:27:24.792
when these images were taken?

547
00:27:25.750 --> 00:27:26.958
Uh...

548
00:27:27.042 --> 00:27:28.833
Yes. I-I was.

549
00:27:28.917 --> 00:27:31.625
So the intention was dull and listless.

550
00:27:31.708 --> 00:27:34.625
I wouldn't say that was.
um. the goal.

551
00:27:34.708 --> 00:27:39.958
And the models were encouraged
to mill around like starving goats

552
00:27:40.042 --> 00:27:43.792
in the parking lot of a methadone clinic
in New Jersey.

553
00:27:44.917 --> 00:27:46.292
- What?
- Can't say that.

554
00:27:46.375 --> 00:27:47.667
What am I not allowed to say?

555
00:27:47.750 --> 00:27:49.000
- Methadone?
- Mmm.

556
00:27:49.083 --> 00:27:51.125
New Jersey?

557
00:27:51.208 --> 00:27:52.042
Anyway...

558
00:27:52.125 --> 00:27:54.250
This was our first time using
this photographer.

559
00:27:54.333 --> 00:27:55.458
so we can do a reshoot.

560
00:27:55.542 --> 00:27:57.208
Just. you know. fix it.

561
00:27:58.208 --> 00:28:02.750
So. who else? Marta?
What do you have cooking?

562
00:28:02.833 --> 00:28:05.208
We're seeing a lot of gorpcore
for this year's resort.

563
00:28:05.292 --> 00:28:09.458
so I was thinking of doing an
interactive piece on the app

564
00:28:09.542 --> 00:28:11.208
where you choose a National Park

565
00:28:11.292 --> 00:28:14.500
and then you choose
a hiking shoe and a bum bag.

566
00:28:14.583 --> 00:28:16.375
A bum bag!

567
00:28:16.458 --> 00:28:19.167
May my suicide be brief and painless.

568
00:28:20.208 --> 00:28:21.708
- No. no.
- What?

569
00:28:21.792 --> 00:28:22.851
What do you mean. "No. no."

570
00:28:22.875 --> 00:28:26.917
I... I'm not talking about
killing other people. Yet.

571
00:28:28.708 --> 00:28:32.292
Okay. Fine. Uh. who else?

572
00:28:32.375 --> 00:28:33.417
Ilana. what do you have?

573
00:28:33.500 --> 00:28:37.292
The re-report of the SpeedFash
story went over well.

574
00:28:37.375 --> 00:28:40.833
Media critics responded to our candor

575
00:28:40.917 --> 00:28:43.125
and to us taking responsibility.

576
00:28:43.208 --> 00:28:46.625
Right. But did anyone read the piece?

577
00:28:46.708 --> 00:28:47.750
I don't know.

578
00:28:47.833 --> 00:28:49.667
Nigel. how are the metrics on that one?

579
00:28:50.208 --> 00:28:52.042
- Mm-mmm.
- Hmm-mmm.

580
00:28:52.667 --> 00:28:58.042
See. you are here to write and edit
features that people read.

581
00:28:58.125 --> 00:29:01.458
And when that happens. yes.
you may interrupt a meeting.

582
00:29:02.208 --> 00:29:04.958
But until then...

583
00:29:05.958 --> 00:29:07.208
Mm-mmm.

584
00:29:08.583 --> 00:29:12.500
Let's talk about rodeo bow ties.

585
00:29:12.583 --> 00:29:13.583
This one's cute.

586
00:29:15.333 --> 00:29:16.458
That was kinda rough.

587
00:29:16.958 --> 00:29:19.458
I mean. I just steered us
through a crisis.

588
00:29:19.542 --> 00:29:21.167
Is it so hard to acknowledge that?

589
00:29:21.250 --> 00:29:24.167
Oh. yes. The girl who likes validation.

590
00:29:24.250 --> 00:29:25.375
Did your parents hang

591
00:29:25.458 --> 00:29:27.333
all of your finger paintings
up on the fridge?

592
00:29:27.417 --> 00:29:28.583
No. It's not that.

593
00:29:28.667 --> 00:29:29.917
I don't need a pat on the head.

594
00:29:30.000 --> 00:29:32.458
I-I-I need to know what she wants.

595
00:29:32.542 --> 00:29:34.667
All right. I need constructive feedback.

596
00:29:34.750 --> 00:29:36.042
Oh. feedback.

597
00:29:36.125 --> 00:29:39.042
And a lollipop. or... just feedback?

598
00:29:40.458 --> 00:29:41.667
Did you need this job?

599
00:29:42.792 --> 00:29:44.208
Did you take the job?

600
00:29:45.083 --> 00:29:47.083
So figure out a way to do this job.

601
00:29:47.167 --> 00:29:48.625
- Bye.
- Bye.

602
00:29:48.708 --> 00:29:50.375
Bye.

603
00:30:21.292 --> 00:30:23.292
Okay. so I think that if
we're talking about...

604
00:30:23.375 --> 00:30:24.768
Kind of follow that sartorial thing

605
00:30:24.792 --> 00:30:26.000
and how it links up to...

606
00:30:51.292 --> 00:30:53.083
What is this?

607
00:30:53.167 --> 00:30:54.542
Oh. that's far too pink. Ken.

608
00:30:54.625 --> 00:30:55.542
We are subtle.

609
00:30:55.625 --> 00:30:57.268
We're not Valentino.
do you know what I mean?

610
00:30:57.292 --> 00:30:59.583
Is this the sample I sent you?
"Tulip whisper."

611
00:30:59.667 --> 00:31:00.667
That's the one.

612
00:31:01.625 --> 00:31:03.958
Now I don't know. I don't know about that.

613
00:31:04.042 --> 00:31:05.292
Wow.

614
00:31:05.375 --> 00:31:06.917
Oh. there she is.

615
00:31:07.667 --> 00:31:08.667
Is this all you?

616
00:31:08.750 --> 00:31:10.875
- It is.
- It's impressive.

617
00:31:10.958 --> 00:31:13.292
You are very busy.
Thank you for your time.

618
00:31:13.375 --> 00:31:16.708
The thinking is that we will
cover the new flagship.

619
00:31:16.792 --> 00:31:18.417
and your role in putting it together.

620
00:31:18.500 --> 00:31:19.625
Is that Miranda's idea?

621
00:31:19.708 --> 00:31:21.000
Um. it was mine.

622
00:31:21.792 --> 00:31:23.833
Fine. If that's what you think
is best. then that...

623
00:31:23.917 --> 00:31:24.958
That's fine.

624
00:31:25.042 --> 00:31:26.518
Okay. great. Why don't you.
uh. give me a tour.

625
00:31:26.542 --> 00:31:27.375
Okay. Will do.

626
00:31:27.458 --> 00:31:30.250
Ken. it is not a whisper.
It's a cry for help.

627
00:31:30.333 --> 00:31:32.917
This. of course. is a tribute to
the grand staircase

628
00:31:33.000 --> 00:31:36.708
at the original Dior Atelier
on Avenue Montaigne.

629
00:31:36.792 --> 00:31:38.750
- This is incredible.
- I know.

630
00:31:38.833 --> 00:31:40.333
And the cost?

631
00:31:40.417 --> 00:31:42.167
I'm not at liberty to discuss that. Andy.

632
00:31:42.250 --> 00:31:44.292
but it is whopping.

633
00:31:44.375 --> 00:31:46.125
What? What is that sickening look?

634
00:31:46.208 --> 00:31:49.667
It's just... It's nice
to see you all grown up.

635
00:31:49.750 --> 00:31:51.667
Ugh. So... So gooey.

636
00:31:51.750 --> 00:31:54.125
Always when you used to make that face...

637
00:31:54.208 --> 00:31:55.726
Because you were always so irritating.

638
00:31:55.750 --> 00:31:57.708
Yeah. you were a barrel of fun.

639
00:31:57.792 --> 00:31:59.833
No. hey. hey. hey. Listen.

640
00:31:59.917 --> 00:32:01.434
I don't know. It's nice to see you again.

641
00:32:01.458 --> 00:32:03.083
- Catch me up. Who are you now?
- No.

642
00:32:03.167 --> 00:32:06.542
Like. not for this. just. human to human.

643
00:32:06.625 --> 00:32:10.333
Fine. I am divorced from
a pathological narcissist. Thank God.

644
00:32:10.417 --> 00:32:11.559
But I've got two beautiful children.

645
00:32:11.583 --> 00:32:12.417
Bronwyn and Roark.

646
00:32:12.500 --> 00:32:13.820
One at Collegiate. one at Chapin.

647
00:32:14.250 --> 00:32:15.917
- Good for you.
- I know. Gorgeous. right?

648
00:32:16.000 --> 00:32:17.292
- Yeah.
- You?

649
00:32:17.375 --> 00:32:20.542
I... left New York for 15 years.

650
00:32:20.625 --> 00:32:23.667
Just lived everywhere. chasing stories.

651
00:32:24.250 --> 00:32:27.250
And I'm not married.
Never found the right person.

652
00:32:27.750 --> 00:32:30.708
And my kids are
at a doctor's office on 85th.

653
00:32:31.208 --> 00:32:32.393
They're frozen eggs right now.

654
00:32:32.417 --> 00:32:34.018
but I like to think of them
as my little ones.

655
00:32:34.042 --> 00:32:35.250
Siobhan and Esther.

656
00:32:36.542 --> 00:32:37.768
Okay. why did you leave <i>Runway</i>?

657
00:32:37.792 --> 00:32:39.250
I'm sorry. is this an exposé?

658
00:32:39.333 --> 00:32:41.226
- No. it's just a question.
- It's not really relevant.

659
00:32:41.250 --> 00:32:44.042
Well. I mean. you worshipped
that place. and Miranda.

660
00:32:44.125 --> 00:32:45.667
So. why'd you leave?

661
00:32:45.750 --> 00:32:47.333
Why are you even asking me why?

662
00:32:47.417 --> 00:32:49.167
I mean. have a perv around this place.

663
00:32:49.250 --> 00:32:52.375
Luxury retail is the only
sector of the fashion business

664
00:32:52.458 --> 00:32:54.542
that still makes money. That's it. Retail.

665
00:32:54.625 --> 00:32:55.684
Everything else. forget it.

666
00:32:55.708 --> 00:32:58.167
So. yes. Happy to be here. frankly.

667
00:32:58.250 --> 00:33:02.333
Because do you know that 20 years ago.
a $100 handbag was considered a splurge?

668
00:33:02.417 --> 00:33:03.857
Brands like us. we changed all that.

669
00:33:04.417 --> 00:33:08.083
Used logos and branding
because everyone understands.

670
00:33:08.167 --> 00:33:09.417
everyone gets it.

671
00:33:09.500 --> 00:33:12.667
that your bag. your scarf.
your perfume. your umbrella...

672
00:33:12.750 --> 00:33:13.583
Write this down.

673
00:33:13.667 --> 00:33:16.583
It tells the world who
you are. what you care about.

674
00:33:16.667 --> 00:33:19.125
And now. there's housewives in Banff

675
00:33:19.208 --> 00:33:21.958
who wouldn't dream of going out
without one of our $3.000 totes.

676
00:33:22.042 --> 00:33:23.042
And that's a good thing?

677
00:33:23.083 --> 00:33:25.768
I don't know. Is it a bad thing
to bring beauty and design to everyone?

678
00:33:25.792 --> 00:33:28.083
Everyone who has $3.000.

679
00:33:28.167 --> 00:33:29.583
Have you heard of Christmas?

680
00:33:30.375 --> 00:33:32.917
Anyway. don't you worry
about me and my career.

681
00:33:33.000 --> 00:33:34.042
Worry about yourself.

682
00:33:34.708 --> 00:33:36.833
I haven't seen any of your
stories get any traction.

683
00:33:36.917 --> 00:33:38.750
Nothing moving the needle there.

684
00:33:39.500 --> 00:33:40.917
What does Miranda say about it?

685
00:33:41.917 --> 00:33:43.083
Is she being tough on you?

686
00:33:45.542 --> 00:33:47.583
It's normal Miranda stuff.

687
00:33:48.208 --> 00:33:53.083
Yes. Irv. Yes. I am looking at
the numbers as we speak.

688
00:33:53.167 --> 00:33:54.167
<i>They're unacceptable.</i>

689
00:33:54.250 --> 00:33:55.750
- <i>Take care of it!</i>
- Okay. I...

690
00:33:59.792 --> 00:34:01.500
Well. that sounded like a warm bath.

691
00:34:01.583 --> 00:34:05.250
It's as if he forgets
he hired her.

692
00:34:06.000 --> 00:34:08.875
His hire. my problem.

693
00:34:08.958 --> 00:34:12.708
Did he say anything at all
about the global editorial job?

694
00:34:12.792 --> 00:34:15.208
No. he's gone mum about all that.

695
00:34:15.292 --> 00:34:17.932
I've spent my career trying to figure out
what people need to know.

696
00:34:18.000 --> 00:34:19.809
now I need to figure out
what people wanna click on.

697
00:34:19.833 --> 00:34:20.833
It's just...

698
00:34:20.917 --> 00:34:23.809
Maybe you just have to figure out
how to do those things at the same time.

699
00:34:23.833 --> 00:34:26.625
You know. like. the smart stuff
and the fun stuff.

700
00:34:27.167 --> 00:34:28.167
Oh. my God.

701
00:34:29.042 --> 00:34:32.208
Hi. there. Hi.
Uh. would you like. uh. uh...

702
00:34:32.292 --> 00:34:35.167
No. Not going to sit.

703
00:34:35.667 --> 00:34:38.375
Um. Irv called frustrated.

704
00:34:38.458 --> 00:34:41.417
Your pieces are not breaking through.

705
00:34:41.917 --> 00:34:43.792
Yeah. no. I... But I do have to say that

706
00:34:43.875 --> 00:34:45.518
I think that some of
these pieces are worthwhile.

707
00:34:45.542 --> 00:34:46.583
Worth whose while?

708
00:34:47.583 --> 00:34:51.375
I mean. that you want to
turn new readers on to <i>Runway.</i>

709
00:34:51.458 --> 00:34:52.667
that's great.

710
00:34:52.750 --> 00:34:55.333
But maybe you don't wanna turn off
the ones we already have.

711
00:34:55.417 --> 00:34:57.792
Yeah. um. I-I didn't wanna...

712
00:34:57.875 --> 00:35:00.667
But we do have some
important work coming up.

713
00:35:00.750 --> 00:35:03.000
- Hmm. Oh. good.
- Uh... Um. I...

714
00:35:04.833 --> 00:35:06.333
I'm doing a Sasha Barnes profile.

715
00:35:10.417 --> 00:35:14.583
You really have an interview set?

716
00:35:15.500 --> 00:35:17.125
Uh. close.

717
00:35:17.208 --> 00:35:19.542
I'm just locking in the
details. but I-I-I have an in.

718
00:35:19.625 --> 00:35:20.833
Hmm.

719
00:35:20.917 --> 00:35:22.542
Sasha Barnes hasn't done press

720
00:35:22.625 --> 00:35:23.875
- in three years.
- Three years.

721
00:35:23.958 --> 00:35:26.042
Bit of a holy grail interview-wise.

722
00:35:26.125 --> 00:35:27.958
It's what makes it so exciting.

723
00:35:28.042 --> 00:35:29.083
So what's your in?

724
00:35:30.000 --> 00:35:31.375
Oh...

725
00:35:31.458 --> 00:35:32.875
I don't have one.

726
00:35:34.083 --> 00:35:35.625
- Here we go.
- No. it's...

727
00:35:35.708 --> 00:35:37.125
God. this house is just... Wow.

728
00:35:37.208 --> 00:35:40.500
{\an8}Even back then. they were
just so insanely rich.

729
00:35:40.583 --> 00:35:41.917
And just so I'm clear.

730
00:35:42.000 --> 00:35:43.625
you have no way to get to Sasha.

731
00:35:43.708 --> 00:35:45.167
but you told Miranda that you do?

732
00:35:45.250 --> 00:35:46.542
Correct.

733
00:35:46.625 --> 00:35:49.167
That's just standing a little
close to the fire. no?

734
00:35:49.833 --> 00:35:51.042
I am the fire.

735
00:35:51.833 --> 00:35:53.125
Don't say that to people.

736
00:35:56.958 --> 00:35:58.542
Oh. yeah. yeah. I know this piece.

737
00:35:58.625 --> 00:36:00.042
This is a Cecily Brown.

738
00:36:00.125 --> 00:36:03.333
It sold for over 600K back in 2009.

739
00:36:03.417 --> 00:36:05.875
Okay. Uh. do you know who sold it to them?

740
00:36:05.958 --> 00:36:07.198
Yeah. probably my friend Paula.

741
00:36:07.250 --> 00:36:08.583
She's Cecily's biggest dealer.

742
00:36:08.667 --> 00:36:09.809
Can she get me Sasha's number?

743
00:36:09.833 --> 00:36:11.958
Maybe. Let me call Paula.

744
00:36:13.125 --> 00:36:14.917
- Can you go faster?
- You gotta chill.

745
00:36:15.000 --> 00:36:16.083
- I know.
- Okay.

746
00:36:16.167 --> 00:36:17.851
Paula said you might be able
to get me a number

747
00:36:17.875 --> 00:36:18.917
for Sasha Barnes.

748
00:36:19.542 --> 00:36:21.750
Uh-huh. You can't.

749
00:36:22.667 --> 00:36:24.833
Dog trainer? I'll take it.

750
00:36:24.917 --> 00:36:26.958
I just wanna ask her some questions.

751
00:36:27.958 --> 00:36:29.917
Yes. no. I promise
it won't get back to you.

752
00:36:30.875 --> 00:36:32.667
Thank you!

753
00:36:33.667 --> 00:36:36.500
Sasha? Hi. Andy Sachs from <i>Runway</i> again.

754
00:36:36.583 --> 00:36:38.500
Uh. would love to talk
when you have a sec.

755
00:36:38.583 --> 00:36:41.792
So call me anytime. Anytime.

756
00:36:41.875 --> 00:36:45.417
I'm always clutching my phone. Thank you.

757
00:36:46.625 --> 00:36:49.250
Sorry. I am so focused on
